

ctvt100
=======

CT VT100 is part of the Terca C++ libraries.
It provides a very simple interface for
utilizing VT100 terminal systems.
This includes loading bars, colors, and
other special effects (see test.cpp for
examples).

Installing
==========

This library uses a standard makefile.
Note that if you are not on a GNU/Linux
system, you will probably need to change
the install directories. You may also
need to change the compiler. The default
is gcc.
To build and install use:

make
sudo make install

Please note that you need to do:
sudo make uninstall
before reinstalling if you decide to make
any changes to CT VT100.

